"{\"uid\": \"horseandhound.co.uk-plus-opinion-nick-skelton-showjumping-paris-olympics-868449\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Nick Skelton, who won team gold at London 2012 and individual gold at Rio 2016, looks beyond some overzealous stewards to a dazzling Paris Games Paris 2024will sit right up there as one of the best Olympics I have been to.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Skelton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nick Skelton\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Skelton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Skelton\"}, {\"begin\": 35, \"end\": 46, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998981366, \"rank\": 1.016589543203757e-10, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 146, \"end\": 151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.828490318645521e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"team gold\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 31}, {\"ngram\": \"Rio 2016\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 78}, {\"ngram\": \"some overzealous stewards\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 118}, {\"ngram\": \"the best Olympics\", \"from\": 189, \"to\": 206}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the excellent facilities for the horses to the beautiful backdrop, the showjumping was superb.\", \"from\": 224, \"to\": 323, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the excellent facilities\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 253}, {\"ngram\": \"the horses\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 268}, {\"ngram\": \"the beautiful backdrop\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 294}, {\"ngram\": \"the showjumping\", \"from\": 296, \"to\": 311}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have always been against the new three-rider team format, much preferring to have a drop score, but it worked really well in Paris with an element of sudden death - one fault and you are out - that made it so exciting.\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 452, \"end\": 457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.828490318645521e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the new three-rider team format\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 383}, {\"ngram\": \"a drop score\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 421}, {\"ngram\": \"an element\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"sudden death - one fault\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have never seen Great Britain's trio ofBen Maher,Scott BrashandHarry Charlesride better, and for Scott to coax every last ounce of reserves from Jefferson - who would be far from an easy ride - under immense pressure to win gold showed superb horsemanship.\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 567, \"end\": 580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9459176918218208, \"rank\": 0.0571505950923692, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"score\": 0.999999857090653, \"rank\": 1.1349040423405323e-07, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\"}, {\"begin\": 648, \"end\": 653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"score\": 0.999999857090653, \"rank\": 1.1349040423405323e-07, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\"}, {\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.062384678372954e-18, \"text\": \"Jefferson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ofBen Maher\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 599}, {\"ngram\": \"every last ounce\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 678}, {\"ngram\": \"reserves\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 690}, {\"ngram\": \"an easy ride\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 742}, {\"ngram\": \"immense pressure\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 779}, {\"ngram\": \"superb horsemanship\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 806}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Course-designers Santiago Varela and Gr\\u00e9gory Bodo deserve a medal too.\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 826, \"end\": 834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\", \"score\": 0.9999977456630348, \"rank\": 2.119039963443933e-06, \"text\": \"Santiago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\"}, {\"begin\": 854, \"end\": 858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boro_people\", \"score\": 0.9999999997808118, \"rank\": 1.8931123096425495e-10, \"text\": \"Bodo\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boro_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boro_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 874}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fences were beautiful and they did an excellent job throughout.\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 947, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The fences\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 890}, {\"ngram\": \"an excellent job\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The final day's track was as big as I have seen but perfectly pitched - to get three clears for three medals is the ultimate goal in course-building but no mean feat.\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 1114, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The final day's track\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 969}, {\"ngram\": \"three clears\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1039}, {\"ngram\": \"three medals\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"the ultimate goal\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"course-building\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1096}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I thoughtSteve Guerdatwas going to win and the crowd really got behind him, but that was a very hard turnback to the vertical in the jump-off.Christian Kukukis a very good rider and has won some big grands prix with Checker 47, so he was a worthy winner.\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1370, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Guerdatwas\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1168}, {\"ngram\": \"a very hard turnback\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1225}, {\"ngram\": \"the vertical\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1241}, {\"ngram\": \"the jump-off\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1257}, {\"ngram\": \"Christian Kukukis\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1275}, {\"ngram\": \"some big grands prix\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1326}, {\"ngram\": \"Checker\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1339}, {\"ngram\": \"a worthy winner\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then forMaikel van der Vleuten to win his second individual Olympic bronze medalis an amazing achievement, albeit with a hint of heartbreak that he's twice come so close to gold.\", \"from\": 1371, \"to\": 1549, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"forMaikel\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"van der Vleuten\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"his second individual Olympic bronze\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1445}, {\"ngram\": \"an amazing achievement\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1476}, {\"ngram\": \"a hint\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1496}, {\"ngram\": \"heartbreak\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1510}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1548}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was such a shame to watch my partnerLaura Krautjust miss out at the last fence in the individual final with Baloutinue, who I'd never seen jump better - such were the highs and lows.\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1738, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such a shame\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1572}, {\"ngram\": \"my partnerLaura\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1597}, {\"ngram\": \"Krautjust\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1607}, {\"ngram\": \"the last fence\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1634}, {\"ngram\": \"the individual final\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"Baloutinue\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1674}, {\"ngram\": \"the highs\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1728}, {\"ngram\": \"lows\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1737}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did smile hearing a BBC presenter say it was Great Britain's first team showjumping gold since 2012 when really it was only our second in 72 years.\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1762, \"end\": 1765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9013080637834913, \"rank\": 0.1086680356786057, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1787, \"end\": 1800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9459176918218208, \"rank\": 0.0571505950923692, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1826, \"to\": 1830}, {\"ngram\": \"72 years\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But we have secured four gold medals at the past four Games, so let us hope our governing bodyBritish Showjumpingcapitalises on this success, gets our shows back on a par with those in mainland Europe and makes us the envy of the world once again.\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 2137, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"four gold medals\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1926}, {\"ngram\": \"the past four Games\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1949}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"bodyBritish Showjumpingcapitalises\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 2014}, {\"ngram\": \"this success\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2030}, {\"ngram\": \"our shows\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2046}, {\"ngram\": \"a par\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2060}, {\"ngram\": \"mainland Europe\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2090}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2103}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Understandably,horse welfarewas at the forefront of everyone's minds at these Games.\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2223, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"horse\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2159}, {\"ngram\": \"the forefront\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2187}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone's minds\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2207}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am all for correct procedures to make sure it remains a top priority, but the only slight dampener in Paris was what I would call some overzealous stewarding.\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2328, \"end\": 2333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.828490318645521e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"correct procedures\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2255}, {\"ngram\": \"a top priority\", \"from\": 2280, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"the only slight dampener\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"some overzealous stewarding\", \"from\": 2356, \"to\": 2383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Take Laura for example - she loves her horses.\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2391, \"end\": 2396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9999996497713868, \"rank\": 3.5022684392944694e-07, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2408}, {\"ngram\": \"her horses\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They follow her round the stable at home, where they receive five-star treatment.\", \"from\": 2433, \"to\": 2514, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her round\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2454}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2473}, {\"ngram\": \"five-star treatment\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But she and these other professional riders were instructed every day as to how they should and should not be working their horses, who, like any human athlete, need their bodies to be stretched, flexed and thoroughly warmed-up.\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2743, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these other professional riders\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2558}, {\"ngram\": \"their horses\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2645}, {\"ngram\": \"any human athlete\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2674}, {\"ngram\": \"their bodies\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are doing nothing wrong, but there is a fear that we could be seen to be by do-gooders who think we use and abuse our beloved horses.\", \"from\": 2745, \"to\": 2881, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2765}, {\"ngram\": \"a fear\", \"from\": 2786, \"to\": 2792}, {\"ngram\": \"do-gooders\", \"from\": 2824, \"to\": 2834}, {\"ngram\": \"our beloved horses\", \"from\": 2862, \"to\": 2880}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the dust has settled on these Games, the FEI needs to look at the blood rule because having it so black and white is not fair.\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 3015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2930, \"end\": 2933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9307567039228728e-32, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the dust\", \"from\": 2889, \"to\": 2897}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 2924}, {\"ngram\": \"the blood rule\", \"from\": 2951, \"to\": 2965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I saw the tiny mark situated under the horse's girth for which Brazil's Pedro Veniss was eliminated in the team contest.\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3079, \"end\": 3085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9704901788214403, \"rank\": 0.030406795811254297, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3088, \"end\": 3100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pedro_Veniss\", \"score\": 0.9999960900994704, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pedro Veniss\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pedro_Veniss\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pedro_Veniss\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the tiny mark\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3035}, {\"ngram\": \"the horse's girth\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3068}, {\"ngram\": \"the team contest\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3135}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a bitter pill to swallow for him.\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3177, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bitter pill\", \"from\": 3144, \"to\": 3157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But imagine if, for example, Scott, having secured gold, had then been found to have a tiny rub mark and they later had to announce their elimination?\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3207, \"end\": 3212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"score\": 0.999999857090653, \"rank\": 1.1349040423405323e-07, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3205}, {\"ngram\": \"secured gold\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3233}, {\"ngram\": \"a tiny rub mark\", \"from\": 3263, \"to\": 3278}, {\"ngram\": \"their elimination\", \"from\": 3310, \"to\": 3327}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the stewards had a direct line to the judges and a video assistant referee (VAR)-style replay available for any horse found to have blood on it, they could look at each case clearly to ascertain where and why it happened.\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3554, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the stewards\", \"from\": 3333, \"to\": 3345}, {\"ngram\": \"a direct line\", \"from\": 3350, \"to\": 3363}, {\"ngram\": \"the judges\", \"from\": 3367, \"to\": 3377}, {\"ngram\": \"a video assistant referee\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3407}, {\"ngram\": \"(VAR)-style replay\", \"from\": 3408, \"to\": 3426}, {\"ngram\": \"any horse\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3450}, {\"ngram\": \"blood\", \"from\": 3465, \"to\": 3470}, {\"ngram\": \"each case\", \"from\": 3497, \"to\": 3506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Occasionally a rider will be at fault, in which case that's a clear elimination, but horses do not jump these huge fences on their own.\", \"from\": 3556, \"to\": 3691, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a rider\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3576}, {\"ngram\": \"fault\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3593}, {\"ngram\": \"which case\", \"from\": 3598, \"to\": 3608}, {\"ngram\": \"a clear elimination\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3635}, {\"ngram\": \"horses\", \"from\": 3641, \"to\": 3647}, {\"ngram\": \"these huge fences\", \"from\": 3660, \"to\": 3677}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you do not help your horse, he's just as likely to land on a back rail and hurt himself, which is far worse than an accidental spur mark.\", \"from\": 3692, \"to\": 3832, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your horse\", \"from\": 3711, \"to\": 3721}, {\"ngram\": \"a back rail\", \"from\": 3754, \"to\": 3765}, {\"ngram\": \"an accidental spur mark\", \"from\": 3808, \"to\": 3831}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We may be walking a tightrope, but in Paris we came together to showcase our sport in an extremely positive light with 20,000 people packing the stands each day in support.\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 4006, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3872, \"end\": 3877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.828490318645521e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a tightrope\", \"from\": 3852, \"to\": 3863}, {\"ngram\": \"our sport\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 3916}, {\"ngram\": \"an extremely positive light\", \"from\": 3920, \"to\": 3947}, {\"ngram\": \"20,000 people\", \"from\": 3953, \"to\": 3966}, {\"ngram\": \"the stands\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 3985}, {\"ngram\": \"support\", \"from\": 3998, \"to\": 4005}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What more could you want?\", \"from\": 4007, \"to\": 4032, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u25cf What was your Paris highlight?\", \"from\": 4034, \"to\": 4066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4050, \"end\": 4055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.828490318645521e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know athhletters@futurenet.com, including your name, nearest town and country, for the chance for your letter to appear in a forthcoming issue of the magazine You might also be interested in: Stay in touch with all the news in the run-up to and throughout the major shows and events during 2025 and beyond with a Horse & Hound subscription.Subscribe todayfor all you need to know ahead of these major events, plus online reports on the action as it happens from our expert team of reporters and in-depth analysis in our special commemorative magazines.\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4397, \"end\": 4410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Horse_&_Hound\", \"score\": 0.9999999999877218, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Horse & Hound\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Horse_&_Hound\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Horse_&_Hound\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4071, \"to\": 4073}, {\"ngram\": \"athhletters@futurenet.com\", \"from\": 4079, \"to\": 4104}, {\"ngram\": \"your name\", \"from\": 4116, \"to\": 4125}, {\"ngram\": \"town\", \"from\": 4135, \"to\": 4139}, {\"ngram\": \"country\", \"from\": 4144, \"to\": 4151}, {\"ngram\": \"the chance\", \"from\": 4157, \"to\": 4167}, {\"ngram\": \"your letter\", \"from\": 4172, \"to\": 4183}, {\"ngram\": \"a forthcoming issue\", \"from\": 4197, \"to\": 4216}, {\"ngram\": \"the magazine\", \"from\": 4220,